<HEADLINE> Twenty-nine Nations Qualified for World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine qualifiers for next
year's France World Cup finals are now known after Japan won the
Asian zone play-off on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The qualifiers will all be completed by November 29 after Iran
and Australia have completed the final playoff over two legs,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Two more qualifiers will be decided later on Sunday when the
final entrants from South America and CONCACAF will be decided.
</P>
<P>
The draw for the finals takes place in Marseille on December 4.
</P>
<P>
Following are the qualifiers for the 1998 World Cup finals:
</P>
<P>
Europe: Auatria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Denmark, England,
France, Germany, Italy, Netherlands, Norway, Romania, Scotland,
Spain, Yugoslavia
</P>
<P>
South America
</P>
<P>
Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Paraguay
</P>
<P>
CONCACAF
</P>
<P>
United States, Mexico
</P>
<P>
Africa
</P>
<P>
Cameroon, Morocco, Nigeria, South Africa, Tunisia
</P>
<P>
Asia
</P>
<P>
Japan, South Korea, Saudi Arabia
</P>
