<HEADLINE> Dalian Wanda Marches ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- League leader Dalian Wanda,
with 11 wins and three draws, came from behind to keep its
unbeaten record intact as China resumed its first division soccer
after the internationals returned to club duties from their
unsuccessful World Cup try.
</P>
<P>
Hao Haidong, top striker in the Chinese team, scored twice to
help the home team Wamda see off the visiting Tianjin Samsung 3-1,
who surprisingly took a 1-0 lead in the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
The victory in Dalian, host site for the Chinese World Cup
campaign, just brought a little consolation to the home crowd, who
suffered a heartbreaking blow as they witnessed their national
team fail to qualify for the World Cup for the fifth time at as
many attempts in history.
</P>
<P>
Last year's runners-up Shanghai Shenhua kept moving up on the
table to the fourth place after a rain-soaked 2-0 win over the
bottom club Guangdong Hongyuan.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Apollo striked a season-high three goals in one game,
beating August First at home. It only managed four goals in the
previous 13 matches.
</P>
<P>
Yanbian Aodong remianed its unbeaten streak this season to 10
matches when the home team took full advantage of the below-zero
cold conditions to win 1-0 over the Southwest China club Sichuang
Quanxing.
</P>
<P>
In day's other matches, Jinan Taishan was forced to a home
goaless draw with Beijing Guo'an on a snow-white ground; Qingdao
Hainiu came from one goal behind to tie Vanguards Huandao 1-1
away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
