<HEADLINE> Milosevic Thinks Highly of China Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, November 16 (Xinhua) -- President of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia Slobodan Milosevic today hailed his China
tour as a great success that marks the start of comprehensive
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic said this on arriving here from his three-day state
visit to China, where he held talks with Chinese leaders and
toured Shanghai, China's largest industrial center.
</P>
<P>
The president, who arrived in Beijing on November 13, said he
is confident that the cooperation, highly important for both
sides, would be further promoted.
</P>
<P>
"China is not only the most populous country in the world, but
also the most successful one judging from many parameters, because
it has achieved an unprecedented economic growth rate in the world
over the past dozen years," he said.
</P>
<P>
It has also made rapid progress in many sectors including high
technologies and telecommunications, he added.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement on cooperation and other important
documents signed by the two sides during his stay in China reflect
their common policies on cooperation and will serve as a basis for
further strengthening the cooperative ties, he noted. 
</P>
