<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice FM on Li Peng's Visit to Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan today said Premier Li Peng's visit to Japan is very
successful and gained important results.
</P>
<P>
Tang, who was with the Chinese premier during the six-day
official good-will visit, made the remark on Li's flight home.
</P>
<P>
The trip, he said, took place on the occasion of the 25th
anniversary of the normalization of the Sino-Japanese diplomatic
ties, and therefore was given high attention by the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The world community was also attentive to the event, he said.
</P>
<P>
During Li's visit, China and Japan reaffirmed their goal of
striving to build good-neighborly cooperative relations oriented
toward the 21th century, the senior Chinese diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
On his part, the Chinese premier put forth five principles as a
guidepost for further expanding the China-Japan ties, and they
were well received by Japanese from all walks of life, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he noted, the two sides reached the consensus that
frequent visits, contacts and dialogues between the two countries'
leaders will be conducive to better mutual understanding and trust.
</P>
<P>
On Japan's part, the government invited Chinese President Jiang
Zemin to visit the country next year on the 20th anniversary of
the signing of the China-Japan Treaty of Peace and Friendship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side has accepted the invitation in principle, the
vice-foreign minister said.
</P>
<P>
Also during Li's visit, China and Japan signed a new fishery
agreement, and reached a cooperation agreement on environmental
protection into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
And in bilateral talks for China's entry into the World Trade
Organization (WTO), the two countries announced major progresses
in the fields of service and trade, and agreed to work for the
early conclusion of bilateral agreements on those issues, he said.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to further deepen and strengthen economic,
scientific and technological cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li toured a number of well-known high-tech Japanese
companies, which expressed their strong willingness to cooperate
with China in high-tech areas, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Japan, the Chinese premier stressed the
importance and the need to enhance the traditional friendly ties
between the two countries, educate young people with correct
historic views and nurture successors for the cause of China-Japan
friendship.
</P>
<P>
These initiatives, Tang said, triggered positive responses from
the Japanese government, its opposition and the general public.
</P>
<P>
As China and Japan are close neighbors and are countries
influential over Asia and the world, he noted, the development of
their good-neighborly friendship and mutually beneficial
cooperation not only benefit the two peoples, but serve the peace
and development across the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed his belief that Li Peng's visit to Japan will
play an important role in promoting the healthy development of
China-Japan ties and in maintaining peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
