<HEADLINE> Japan qualifies for World Cup finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Japan qualified for the
World Cup finals for the first time in history by edging Iran 3-2
in sudden death extra time Sunday in the World Cup Asian Zone
play-off in Johor Bahru, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Masayuki Okano helped the 2002 World Cup host securing its
first World Cup ticket by scoring the golden goal 25 minutes into
extra time after the two sides were deadlocked in 2-2 during the
normal time.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Masashi Nakayama opened the scoring in the 40th minute
before the Iranian striker Khoadadad Azizi equalized one minute
into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Ali Daei put Iran 2-1 ahead at the 52th minute, only to see
Japan equalize again through Shoji Jo in the 75th minute.
</P>
<P>
Iran will take on the Oceania group winner Australia for the
last ticket on a home-and-away format on November 22 and November
29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
