<HEADLINE> Guangdong Hosts International Chaozhou Studies Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Second International
Chaozhou Studies Seminar closed today in Shantou, Guangdong
Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 160 Chinese and foreign researchers attending the two-day
seminar discussed various theses on the latest breakthrough in
highly specialized academic area.
</P>
<P>
The seminar focused on the evolution of Chaozhou Studies, as
well as research into the history, culture, geography and folk
customs of Chaozhou, the commercial and maritime hub in ancient
China and the hometown of millions of overseas Chinese.
</P>
