<HEADLINE> Russia Coach Blamed For World Cup Failure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia coach Boris Ignatyev
laid himself open to the criticism from Russia's top football
officials and media on Monday for his country's failure to qualify
for the World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
Russia Football Union chief Vyacheslav Koloskov scolded
Ignatyev for his indecision in working out the best line-up,
lamenting that Russia should have avoided the play-off with Italy
and qualify automatically from its original group, one of the
weakest in the European zone.
</P>
<P>
Russia media were equally scathing, saying that the Russia
coach had committed tactical failings.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in 20 years that Russia or the Soviet
Union have failed to qualify for the World Cup finals after Russia
lost 2-1 overall to Italy in their play-off. 
