<HEADLINE> HK Appoints Officials of Estate Agents Authority </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Tung Chee Hwa has appointed
Marvin Cheung Kin-tung as chairman of the newly-established Estate
Agents Authority (EAA) and Moses Cheng Mo-chi as his deputy, a
senior official said today.
</P>
<P>
Tung also named 18 ordinary members of the EAA, which was set
up in late October amid the ups and downs in the local stock
market. Its main functions were "to regulate the conduct of estate
agents and to devise a licensing system for estate agents."
</P>
<P>
While making efforts to stabilize the share market, the
government of the Special Administrative Region (SAR) has paid
more attention to the housing prices and estate problems.
</P>
<P>
The appointments were announced earlier today by Secretary for
Housing Dominic Wong, who said that the newly-appointed officials
would serve for a period of two years with effect from November 1.
</P>
<P>
The EAA has a wide participation of people from different
spheres of life, including estate agents, property developers,
legal professionals, a surveyor, consumer affairs personnel, an
accountant, a public affairs consultant, businessmen, provisional
legislators and government officials "responsible for overseeing
estate agency development and regulation," Wong said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "The EAA will therefore have a good balance of
different interests."
</P>
<P>
According to him, the newly-formed body will hold its first
meeting very soon and "it will take about a year for the EAA to
devise the necessary regulations, rules and guidelines under the
Estate Agents Ordinance." 
</P>
</TEXT>
