<HEADLINE> Small Enterprises for Sale in Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The city government of
Shenyang, capital of Northeast China's Liaoning Province, plans to
list shares in 192 small state and collective enterprises, a move
which signals the first step in restructuring the ownership of
industrial enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises in question come from the light industry,
machine-building, pharmaceutical, metallurgical, electronics,
chemical, textile, agricultural equipment and building materials
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xizhi, director of the City Commission on Economic System
Restructuring, told participants in a recent work conference that
ownership reform has been introduced to 1,128 industrial
enterprises, or some 29 percent of the city's total number of
related enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The local government will work out preferential regulations for
buyers of the small enterprises in terms of capital transfers,
land leases, tax turnover, placement of employees and other
business practices. 
