<HEADLINE> Abacha Appraises Nigeria's Economic Achievement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Head of State,
General Sani Abacha today praised his government's economic
achievement in an early morning broadcast marking the fourth
anniversary of his leadership.
</P>
<P>
He said the Nigerian economy as a whole has been recording a
steady growth of approximately four percent per annum while
foreign investment in Nigeria last year was the highest in
Africa.
</P>
<P>
In the past four years, the inflation rate has fallen from
over 100 percent to 10 percent, and the exchange rate has been
maintained at around 80 Naira to one U.S. Dollar, all indicating
the government's success in stablizing the economy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Abacha also praised his government's tight fiscal discipline.
"The massive deficits of the past have been completely turned
into a surplus," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the external sector, he said Nigeria's foreign reserves are
at an all-time high while its foreign debt was reduced from three
billion to less than 28 billion Dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
He also listed the major projects carried out by his
government. Among them is the 550 million Dollars Escravos Gas
Plant which marks the first solid step Nigeria has taken to
develop its abundant natural gas resources.
</P>
<P>
Abacha disclosed that in 1998 more emphasis will be placed on
electric power generation to ensure adequate and uninterrupted
supply nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The government will also take steps to revitalize the steel
industry and establish more export process zones, he said.
</P>
