<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting on Common Security in Africa Opens in Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 17 (Xinhua)-- The annual policy meeting on
Common Security and Civil Society in Africa opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting is organised jointly by the Common Security
Forum and the Nordic Africa Institute with the support of the
Swedish Ministry for Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The central themes of the meeting are African views of
democratic political culture; economic, political and humanitarian
aspects of security in Africa; and Africa's role in preventing
violent conflict.
</P>
<P>
The current reconsideration of relations between Africa and
Sweden as described in "Partnership Africa" will also be
discussed.
</P>
<P>
Around 60 Swedish and foreign politicians, diplomats,
researchers and representatives of NGOs attended the meeting.
</P>
