<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Rebound Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices
rebounded sharply today to close at 10,419.75 points as primary
interest rates eased.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index, which traced the performance of 33
blue chips, broke the 10,000-point benchmark by surging 462.42
points, the ninth biggest single-day gain in history.
</P>
<P>
Herbert Lau, an analyst of Vickers Ballas Hong Kong Limited,
said: "The interest rates are stable at around ten percent today,
creating a good market sentiment for property and finance
sectors."
</P>
<P>
The primary three-month interbank lending rates hit 15 percent
early last week and went down to about 10 percent at the weekend.
Property led the rebound by rocketing 773.65 points today, and
finance shares gained 574.62 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover shrank to 11.1 billion HK dollars (1.4 billion U.S.
dollars), showing that investors still stand sideline to watch the
market direction.
</P>
<P>
"The outlook is not clear and the market is still volatile for
the fear that further speculative attacks might push up the
interest rates again," said Lau.
</P>
<P>
Interest rates were jacked up to record high as the Hong Kong
Monetary Authority tried to fend off currency speculators in
October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
