<HEADLINE> Russian official Elaborates Position on Caspian Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia will not allow the
United States to strengthen its position in the oil zone in the
Caspian Sea, First Deputy Prime Minister Boris Nemtsov said today.
</P>
<P>
In a televised interview, Nemtsov indicated that Russia should
act as a leading member in the sea.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the oil exploitation in the Caspian, he said
Russia has missed an opportunity and allowed the United States to
take the lead in joint oil exploration with Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Russia can only make up for the losses by developing Iran's
oilfields, Nemtsov said, adding Russian oil firms should
participate in the development of the oilfields in the Caspian.
</P>
<P>
The Caspian Sea, the largest landlocked sea in the world, has
proven oil reserves of 28 billion barrels and a large amount of
natural gas resources.
</P>
<P>
As one of the five littoral states, Russia holds that the
Caspian natural resources should only be jointly explored by the
littoral countries. The other four are Kazakhstan, Turkmenistan,
Azerbaijan and Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
