<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overturned Bus Kills 17 in North Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people died
instantly while eight others were seriously injured after a
mini-bus overturned at noon of Sunday in north Tanzania's Mara
Region, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The Mara Regional Police Commander, Josiah Mwesiga, told the
press over the telephone that the mini-bus had hit an embankment
at a road junction some five kilometers from the town of Tarime.
</P>
<P>
Eleven of the deceased, including the driver, have been
identified, Mwesiga said, adding that the police has appealed to
residents to visit the district hospital in Tarime to help
identify the other six dead persons.
</P>
<P>
The eight injured people suffered from fractures of their
limbs, he said. However, some people's health were reported to
have been improving steadily.
</P>
<P>
The police is still investigating the circumstances of the
accident, but speedy driving is probably to have led to the
tragedy.
</P>
<P>
The accident was the worst in the region in two years after 18
people died and 50 others were injured when their bus collided
head-on with a Landrover at Kibakari village. 
</P>
</TEXT>
