<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Arrest of Diplomat in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November (Xinhua) -- Iran had denied the reports that
one of its diplomats was arrested in Moscow for attempting to
secure missile know-how, the official news agency IRNA reported
today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference Sunday, Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi confirmed the arrest of an Iranian
citizen in Russia, but said that the detainee was not a staff
member of the Iranian Embassy in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
He described the claim that the person was trying to secure
missile technology for Iran as "baseless," saying that
Iranian-Russian cooperation in all fields was aboveboard.
</P>
<P>
He accused Israel of spreading the rumor as part of its
propaganda campaign to divert international attention from its
expansionist policy in the occupied Arab land.
</P>
<P>
But so far no details were available about the arrest of the
Iranian national in Russia. 
