<HEADLINE> Israel: Not Against Regional Conference Hosted by </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Israel said today that it will
not oppose the holding of next year's Middle East and North
Africa (MENA) economic conference in the Palestinian self-rule
area.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Minister of Industry and Trade Natan Sharansky was
commenting on a proposal put forward at the on-going three-day
Doha MENA conference, which opened here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Palestine is one of the options for the next MENA gathering,
but "the question is open," Sharansky told reporters here. But he
did not give further details.
</P>
<P>
Behind the proposal favoring Palestine as the next host are
apparently some considerations concerning the stalled Mideast
peace process due to Israel's hardline policy, observers said.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the Arab countries are boycotting the Doha
conference because of Israel's participation. Therefore, the Doha
gathering, the fourth in a series, has been downgraded from a
summit to a ministerial one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
