<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Slightly Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices slipped lower
in light trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index (STII) fell by 1.61 points to close at
1698.65 points today.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that the investors' sentiment stayed bearish
despite the better-than-expected 10.1 percent rise in the third
quarter gross domestic product (GDP) figures for the Singapore
economy, which were announced earlier today.
</P>
<P>
The STI index failed to stay above the 1700 level as investors
remained focused on negative news, they said.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 123.45 million units,
valued at 286.46 million Singapore dollars (181.3 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 206 to 118, while 288 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Westmont Land was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 7.7 million units. It was followed by the
Singapore Telecom which had 5.4 million shares traded. Sateras
Res. was next with 4.53 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.5 dollars to end at 45 Singapore dollars.
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign gained 80 cents to
close at 21.3 Singapore dollars, while the Thai Prime Fund
increased by 50 cents to finish at 5.7 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, IPCO was the biggest loser as it declined by
96 cents to close at three U.S. dollars. Innovest Bhd fell by 56
cents to finish at 3.32 Singapore dollars, while the Hong Kong
Land warrant98 lost 54 cents to end at 0.15 U.S. dollar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
