<HEADLINE> Philippines to Conduct Cloud-Seeding to Induce Rains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos has ordered the military to conduct cloud-seeding to induce
artificial rains to ease the effect of El Nino, a senior military
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Staff of the Armed Forces Arnulfo Acedera said the
order came today after Ramos approved the release of 131 million
pesos (4 million U.S. dollars) to finance the cloud-seeding
operations.
</P>
<P>
Acedera said that prior to the operations, the armed forces
would first manufacture the must-needed nucleating agents and
acquire burner gas to gasify the agents.
</P>
<P>
"Cloud-seeding operations will continue as long as there is a
need for artificial simulation of rains," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines, being hit by drought, is facing a water
crisis. President Ramos has called the public to conserve and
recycle water and speed up the construction of irrigation projects
in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
