<HEADLINE> Guiyang-Zunyi Highway Starts Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- A 155.30-km highway
between Guiyang and Zunyi in southwestern China's Guizhou Province
has been completed and has begun operation.
</P>
<P>
The highway is the longest and most difficult to build and the
highest-level in the state rating system among the province's
existing roads.
</P>
<P>
The Guiyang-Zunyi highway is an important component of the
planned sea outlet transportation network in southwestern China,
local official said. The highway network is expected to boost the
economy of Guizhou, a province with scarce resources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
