<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Poland Issue Joint Communique  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China and Poland issued a
joint communique in Beijing today, expressing satisfaction over
Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski's current China visit at
the invitation of President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang and President Kwasniewski held talks this
morning and, according to the communique, the two leaders
exchanged views on bilateral relations and international issues of
common concern.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the governments of the two countries signed a
cooperative agreement on animal quarantines and sanitation, and an
executive plan on cultural and scientific coordination from 1998
to 2000. Both sides hold that the present visit will have an
important impact on further development of their friendly
cooperation, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Both countries agreed that developing their cooperation in
various fields is a common aspiration of their peoples which
complies with the fundamental interest of the two countries and is
beneficial to the peace and development of Asia as well as Europe,
it noted.
</P>
<P>
The two countries stressed that they will develop long-term and
stable cooperative relations based on the universally-recognized
principles of international law. They also expressed a willingness
to increase their political dialogues, according to the communique.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, both sides agreed that developing bilateral economic
and trade ties is an important part of bilateral relations, and
the two countries will encourage direct contact between their
companies and enterprises, try to expand bilateral trade volume
and to keep a balance.
</P>
<P>
The communique further noted that both countries agreed to
conduct cooperation into new industrial and technological fields,
support mutual investment, encourage cooperation in the third
market, and carry out coordination in the financial sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971117.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenyang Develops Foreign Property Rights Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The Property Rights Trade
Center in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning
Province, has opened an agency in the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
The trade center has also opened agencies in the United States,
Japan, Singapore and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The ROK agency will be responsible for organizing enterprise
mergers, property rights transfers and sales of shares and
protecting the rights of creditors.
</P>
<P>
The trade center, founded in 1994 by the provincial government,
provides wide-ranging services, including asset evaluations, legal
consulting and training property rights brokers.
</P>
<P>
The center's 11 members mainly include investment and
securities companies, and medium- to large-sized enterprises.
</P>
