<HEADLINE> Most New Zealanders Want Early Election: Pool </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, November 17 (Xinhua) -- A majority of New
Zealanders prefer a general election sooner than later, according
to the latest opinion pool.
</P>
<P>
The pool, conducted by One Network News Colmar Brunton pool
from November 10 to 13, revealed that only 35 percent of those
surveyed said they wanted the government to run its full term of
three years, TVNZ reported tonight.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-four percent wanted an early election, with 30 percent
hoping it to be held as soon as possible, and 18 percent within
six months.
</P>
<P>
The poll also showed that if an election is held now, the
opposition Labor Party would become the largest party in
Parliament, winning 58 of the 120 seats.  
