<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Herbal Medicine Seeds Return from Space Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists today
obtained the second-generation seeds of a popular Chinese herbal
medicine after exposure to radiation in outer space.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said it is the first time in the world that
Chinese herbal-medicine seeds were treated in a retrievable
satellite resulting in better quality seeds.
</P>
<P>
The space breeding of herbal-medicine seeds is of epoch-making
importance, experts said, and the next step involves production
of medical herbs in other countries.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhongshen, director of the Biological Medicine Center of
Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, said the
space-treated seeds of Huangqin or bailkal skullcap root, are
apparently different from ordinary ones.
</P>
<P>
He said the germination period of the space-treated seeds is
much shorter than that of the ordinary ones and that the space
seeds have longer and stronger roots and the stems are taller.
</P>
<P>
The Huangqin root seeds were carried by China's JB retrievable
satellite for a 15-day space journey. Scientists said the
chromosome distortion of the space seeds make their quality much
better.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese herbal medicines have been applied for treating a
variety of diseases for more than 2,500 years and the Huangqin is
one of the most commonly used herbal medicines among 400 kinds of
commonly used herbal medicines.
</P>
<P>
Doctors practicing traditional Chinese medicine said Huangqin
effectively clears away heat and toxins. It is being used in more
than 40 percent of traditional Chinese medical prescriptions.
</P>
<P>
Its herbal medicine could be used for treatment of pneumonia,
infection of the respiratory tract, high blood pressure, nephritis
and hepatitis.
</P>
<P>
The herbal medicine could be harvested after three or four
years; the wild ones have been sharply reduced due to
overpicking.
</P>
<P>
In usual cases the main stem of the Huangqin would become
withered. The man-plant Huangqin breed is in its third year of
growth.
</P>
<P>
To alter its structure, Chinese scientists began to breed space
seeds to improve the herbal medicine's quality.
</P>
<P>
The Huangqin space seed project is expected to take four years
to complete.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has successfully launched space-seed breeding of
51 varieties of crops.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
