<HEADLINE> Zengcheng Overhauls Agricultural Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Zengcheng, a city in south
China's Pearl River Delta, has made great strides in high-yield,
high-quality and highly efficient agriculture in the process of
rural industrialization.
</P>
<P>
Based on its natural conditions, the city has built up six
production centers for high-quality rice, litchi, vegetables,
fast-growing forest trees, aquatic products and livestock.
</P>
<P>
The city has owned 74 agricultural enterprises, 12 of which
were invested by foreign investors with more than 36 million
U.S. dollars of contractual funds.
</P>
<P>
The city has invested 38 million yuan (4.75 million
U.S. dollars) in 54 agricultural projects with each involving
300,000 yuan (37,500 U.S. dollars) of investment in the first half
of this year.
</P>
<P>
So far, 16 towns of the city have established their
agricultural trade markets and 80 percent of agricultural products
are sold in the markets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city would establish a large wholesale center
of agricultural products this year, co-operating with provinces of
Hainan, Hunan and Jiangxi.  
</P>
