<HEADLINE> Gov't Instability May Be Cause of Industrial Slump: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Indian Finance Minister P.
Chidambaram has for the first time admitted that the instability
of the present United Front government may be the cause of the
steady slowdown in the country's industrial growth.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the state television Doordarshan to be
telecast later today, Chidambaram blamed the Indian industry for
failure to capitalize on the government's incentives for reviving
growth.
</P>
<P>
A finance minister can only do four things -- bringing down the
interest rates, providing more funds to banks by cutting the
reserve ratios, providing enough foreign exchange for any imports,
and bringing the inflation down, he said.
</P>
<P>
Normally all this should spur growth, he said, suggesting that
the measures taken by the government have so far failed to
accelerate growth.
</P>
<P>
The 13-party United Front formed a minority coalition
government in June last year with outside support from the
Congress party.  
