<HEADLINE> People's Daily hails Chinese Premier's Japan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China's "People's Daily" in an
editorial today hailed the just-ended visit to Japan by Chinese
Premier Li Peng as a complete success, calling for promotion of
Sino-Japanese friendship and cooperation from generation to
generation.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of the Japanese government, Premier Li Peng
paid an official good-will visit to Japan from November 11 to 16,
and was accorded warm welcome and hospitality by the Japanese
government, the opposition and personages of various circles, the
editorial said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit by a head of the Chinese government to
Japan in eight years.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Premier Li Peng and Japanese Prime Minister
Ryutaro Hashimoto held cordial and frank talks on bilateral
relations and international and regional issues of common concern,
and reached common understanding in a broad way.
</P>
<P>
Through frequent contacts Li Peng made many friends with
Japanese statesmen, businessmen and people from Japan-China
friendship organizations.
</P>
<P>
"The visit has attained the goal of deepening understanding,
enhancing friendship and strengthening cooperation, which will
produce a far-reaching influence on the consolidation and further
development of China-Japan relations," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 25th anniversary of the normalization of
diplomatic relations between China and Japan. The Sino-Japanese
ties are standing at a crucial point which links the past with the
future, it said.
</P>
<P>
Both the Chinese and Japanese leaders stressed the need to
usher the sound and stable China-Japan relations into the 21st
century and to make great efforts to achieve the goal of
generation-to-generation friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng announced at a press conference five basic principles
for the development of China-Japan relations. They are mutual
respect and non-interference in each other's internal affairs;
seeking common ground while reserving differences and properly
handling the differences; increasing dialogues and mutual
understanding; promoting economic cooperation on the basis of
mutual benefit; and looking to the future and fostering
generation-to-generation friendship.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government put forward the five principles from a
long-term strategic perspective, in accordance with the
Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the China-Japan Treaty of Peace
and Friendship, and after reviewing the positive and negative
experiences in the development of bilateral ties since the
normalization of diplomatic relations between the two countries 25
years ago," the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
They are important guiding principles in the development of the
China-Japan ties at the current stage and in the long-time future.
</P>
<P>
Expanding and promoting economic, trade, scientific and
technological cooperation between the two countries is one of the
major aims of this tour of Japan by Premier Li Peng, it said.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan signed agreements on fishery and cooperation in
environmental protection, and confirmed the major advancement in
the bilateral negotiations on service trade, which is one aspect
of China's entry into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Li also visited a number of well-known enterprises in Japan,
particularly those high-tech industries, getting to know about the
state-of-the-art achievements made by Japan in the field of
science and technology. The Chinese premier also held in-depth
discussions with Japanese businessmen on the new fields, new ways
and new starting points for the promotion of economic cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China, the biggest developing country in the world, and Japan,
one of the most-developed economies in the world, have broad
prospects and great potential in their economic cooperation. China
is a key trading partner for Japan and vice versa. And the two
economies are highly complementary to each other. Li Peng's visit
has given a great impetus to the further economic and
technological cooperation between the two countries, the editorial
added.
</P>
<P>
The development of the bilateral relations in the past 25 years
has proved that strictly abiding by the Sino-Japanese Joint
Declaration and the China-Japan Treaty of Peace and Friendship is
the guarantee of sound and stable development of the relations
between the two countries, it said.
</P>
<P>
The existing problems and those likely to arise in the future
between the two nations should be properly handled through
dialogue and consultations and by seeking common ground while
reserving differences so that they will not become obstacles in
the way of developing bilateral relations, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Japan are influencial countries in Asia and the
world at large. With the profound changes in the internatioal
situation, and the growing trend of multi-polarization, continuous
consolidation and development of good-neighborly, friendly and
cooperative relations between China and Japan not only conform
with the fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also
benefit peace and prosperity in the Asia-Pacific region and the
world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
As Japan chose a way of peaceful development after World War II
and gained successes in economy, "We hope Japan will learn from
the history and continue to follow the way of peaceful
development. We believe that only properly handling the
orientation of developing the Sino-Japanese relations can the
bilateral ties develop in a sound and stable way," the editorial
concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
