<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Army Launches New Phase of Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday morning launched the third phase of their major northern
operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain of Victory) to clear Tamil rebels
from the main highway between the north and the south through
rebel-held areas.
</P>
<P>
According to press reports reaching here today, the troops
recaptured the center of Puliyankulam, one of the major towns on
the highway which was occupied by the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Operation Jaya Sikuru was started on May 13 this year and the
troops had earlier completed two of its phases. The third phase
aims to recapture the remaining stretch of the land route which
runs from the town of Vavuniya to the northern Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The troops recaptured the Jaffna peninsula in May last year and
subsequently cleared the route between the south of the peninsula
and the town of Kilinochchi north of Vavuniya.
</P>
<P>
The troops backed by artillery and air cover were moving
towards Kilinochchi, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government is keen to clear the highway of
rebels to ensure a supply route to the north both for military
supplies and essentials for the civilians.
</P>
<P>
For a long time supplies have been transported by air and sea
which has been very costly for the government.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
