<HEADLINE> Shantou Private Economy Develops Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The private economy in
Shantou, a special economic zone in south China's Guangdong
province, has witnessed an annual growth rate of over 25 percent
in recent years, with the sector emerging as an economic pillar in
the city.
</P>
<P>
The city's over 60,000 private enterprises employ over 400,000
people. Five private Shantou enterprises have total fixed assests
of over 100 million yuan (12.5 million US dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
Shantou's private enterprises had a total 1996 industrial
output value of 40 billion yuan and export volume of 1.1 billion
US dollars, with profits and taxes surpassing one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Profitable private enterprises in the city have not only
established branches in the United States, Thailand, Singapore and
Hong Kong, but have also expanded their presence in the domestic
market.
</P>
<P>
The city's private enterprises invested some 500 million yuan
in technological renovation projects during 1996, with well over
70 percent of the investments used for the development of new
technology and products.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 alone, private enterprises contributed more than 120
million yuan to public welfare programs and 60 million yuan to
help farmers escape poverty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
