<HEADLINE> Idle State-Owned Assets Auctioned in Shanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, November 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 5,600 pieces of
machinery left idle in state-owned enterprises were recently
auctioned at a fair held in Yuncheng, in north China's Shanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, held as part of the city's new round of reform
designed to reallocate idle state-owned assets, attracted over 100
representatives from the nation's machine-building, chemical,
textile, construction, and printing and dyeing sectors.
</P>
<P>
The auction offered machinery valued at 70 million yuan (8.4
million US dollars), with the gavel falling on machinery valued at
over three million yuan. The fair also ended with scores of
letters of intent for future purchases of equipment.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey jointly conducted by the city's Financial
Bureau and the State Assets Management Bureau, revealed that some
two billion yuan of Yuncheng's total seven billion yuan worth of
equipment of state-owned assests remain idle. 
</P>
