<HEADLINE> Hungarian Voters Approve NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian voters are in
favour of the country's plan to join the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO), the results of a referendum showed today.
</P>
<P>
With more than 99 percent of the votes counted, 85.33 percent
had voted for NATO membership. Forty-nine percent of Hungary's
eight million eligible voters took part in the referendum.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference, Prime Minister Gyula Horn hailed the
historical importance of the event, saying that it was the first
time the Hungarian people were asked if they wanted to join a
military bloc.
</P>
<P>
NATO extended invitations to Hungary, the Czech Republic and
Poland in summer this year. 
</P>
