<HEADLINE> Rising City Steps up Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shanwei in south
China's Guangdong province has fulfilled this year's export target
three months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The city had 315 million US dollars worth of imports and
exports by the end of September, an increase of 142.5 percent over
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Exports were worth 248 million U.S dollars and consisted mainly
of clothing, handicrafts, and mechanical, electronic, metal, and
chemical products.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the city's most important trading partner.
</P>
<P>
The success can be attributed to the city government's efforts
to improve the quality of products, optimize the structure of
production, develop overseas markets, and hold economic and trade
fairs. 
