<HEADLINE> Jamaica Book Place in World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KINGSTON, Jamaica, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Jamaica booked a
place in the World Cup finals Sunday as a 0-0 tie with Mexico was
enough for their qualification for the '98 France.
</P>
<P>
Alongside with the United States and Mexico, Jamaica is the
only Caribbean team who claimed a spot in the tournament in the
past 24 years.
</P>
<P>
With Mexico already qualifying and El Salvador needing a win
over the United States and Jamaica's lose, the goalless match was
more like a friendly, as both sides made little efforts for
scoring.
</P>
<P>
Mexican keeper Osvaldo Sanchez stopped a free kick at the 15th
minute and dispersed Linval Dixon's drive one minute later, while
Mexico's best chance came as Luis Garcia's shot barely deflected
in the 55 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other World Cup qualifying matches, Japan beat
Iran 3-2 with a golden goal in the extra time and Chile upset
Bolivia 3-0 to earn a spot in finals.
</P>
<P>
Two-game home-and-away playoffs between Iran and Australian
will complete the 32-team list for the world soccer premier
showcase next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
