<HEADLINE> Popular Science Writers Receive National Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- Nine popular science writers
and editors have received the National Awards for Science and
Technology Achievements for their contribution to the spreading of
knowledge among Chinese readers.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily reported that the nine people received the
awards at a conference held in Beijing Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They compiled two books covering Chinese history of science and
technology and introduction of high technology.
</P>
<P>
Another 22 books were also given awards Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the government will further promote the practice
of science and technology awards designed to stimulate writers to
write more popular science books, said Wang Baoqing, director of
the Office for the National Science and Technology Awards under
the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The conference was held to highlight books on scientific
knowledge dissemination for 1996-1997.
</P>
<P>
Wang emphasised that "spreading scientific knowledge is
important to upgrading laborers' skills and the nation's cultural
qualities. We encourage science writers to produce more books,
especially books involving environment, ecological agriculture and
sustainable development."
</P>
<P>
The National Awards for Science and Technology Achievements,
together with the National Awards for Scientific Invention, are
the country's top honors authorized by the State Council about a
decade ago. 
</P>
