<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 01:30 GMT, November 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his Ukrainian
counterpart Leonid Kuchma held informal talks here Sunday on
mutual exemption from Value Added Tax in the bilateral trade,
local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents also discussed the implementation of the
accords reached between Russia and Ukraine during Yeltsin's visit
to Kiev in May as well as the preparations for Kuchma's official
visit to Moscow scheduled for next January.
(Russia-Ukraine-Informal Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein said Sunday that Iraq
does not want to have a military conflict with the United States.
</P>
<P>
Saddam said during a cabinet meeting tonight that Iraq is ready
to address the problem of implementing U.N. resolutions through
dialogue while stressing that Iraq would not accept any other
solutions to the current crisis, according to Iraqi News Agency.
(Iraq-Saddam-Resolution)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British Chancellor of the Exchequer Gordon Brown is
to oppose a Franco-German proposal to set up an inner circle of
countries to plan the single European currency at Monday's
European Union (EU) finance ministers meeting in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports said Sunday that Paris and Bonn want only
the countries which sign up for the European economic and monetary
union (EMU) at the start of 1999 to be part of the "Euro club."
(Europe-UK)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his visiting
Ukrainian counterpart, Leonid Kuchma, Sunday reached an agreement
on fully abolishing value added tax on production supplies between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the Interfax news agency, the agreement initiated
by the Russian president was reached during a stroll of the two
presidents immediately after Kuchma arrived in Russia Sunday
afternoon. (Russia-Ukraine-Accord)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUANDA -- The Angolan Social Democratic Party (PSDA) urged the
former rebel party here Sunday to cooperate with the government in
re-establishing local governments in areas under its control.
</P>
<P>
Nzuzi Nsumbo, deputy chairman of PSDA, one of the major parties
in the country, made the statement at a ceremony marking the
eighth anniversary of the founding of the party.
</P>
<P>
He demanded UNITA, the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola, to offer the actual number of army it now
has to the UN supervision team, so to facilitate the disarmament
of UNITA according to the 1994 Lusaka Peace Protocol.
(Angola-Appeal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister
Tang Jiaxuan said Sunday Premier Li Peng's visit to Japan is very
successful and gained important results.
</P>
<P>
The trip, he said, took place on the occasion of the 25th
anniversary of the normalization of the Sino-Japanese diplomatic
ties, and therefore was given high attention by the two
countries. (China-Li Peng-Japan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DOHA -- Emir of Qatar Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa al-Thani Sunday
denounced the Israeli intransigent policies towards the Middle
East peace process and called on the United States to push it
forward.
</P>
<P>
This came in a speech by Sheik Hamad at the opening session of
the fourth Middle East and North Africa (MENA) Economic Conference
in Qatari capital Doha.
</P>
<P>
He also called on all peace-loving nations and peoples to do
their best to push forward the peace process in accordance with
the foundations endorsed by the United Nations. (Qatar-MENA
Economic Conference) 
</P>
