<HEADLINE> Chile Qualify for World Cup Finals by Beating Bolivia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Chile claimed the fourth and
last berth in the World Cup South American zone on Sunday through
a 3-0 win over Bolivia after missed the finals for 16 years.
</P>
<P>
Rodrigo Barrera put the hosts ahead in the 24th minute. Chile
made a fine counter-attack as a response for Bolivians' solid
control in midfield with Barrera beating goalie Carlos Trucco.
</P>
<P>
"Matador" Marcelo Salas made it 2-0 four minutes before the
break when he collected the pass from Cristian Castaneda and beat
the Bolivian defenders.
</P>
<P>
Second half substitute Carreno headed home the third goal at
the 49th minute to seal the perfect victory for Chile. Three
Bolivians were sent off in the second half.
</P>
<P>
The other three qualifiers in South America are Argentina,
Colombia and Paraguay. Brazil qualify automatically as the
defending champions. 
</P>
