<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Vaccinate Children Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Health
(MOH) will vaccinate 60 million children aged four and below in
the next two months to prevent communicable polio.
</P>
<P>
Children in 20 provinces and autonomous regions as well as all
children in transient families will be given oral polio vaccines
twice, on December 5 and January 5, according to a report in
today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Eighty million children below four years old have taken the
sugar-coated polio vaccine twice a year since 1993. Wild polio
virus has not been detected nationwide since 1995, other than four
children in border areas of Yunnan Province, who were affected by
the wild polio virus while staying in the neighboring Myanmar, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has decided to continue the supplementary polio
vaccination program in the coming years. And some United Nations
agencies and a number of overseas organizations have donated three
million US dollars to buy vaccines for this year's winter action,
a MOH official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
To stop wild polio virus from crossing borders, China and
Myanmar have agreed to coincide national immunization drives and
exchange epidemic situations regularly, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
