<HEADLINE> Second-hand Motor Vehicle Market Brisk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 17 (Xinhua) -- The annual transaction volume
for second-hand motor vehicles has topped 400,000, with the sales
topping 11 billion yuan (1.325 billion U.S. dollars), according to
the Ministry of Internal Trade.
</P>
<P>
The used motor vehicles market includes registered cars,
tractors, and motorcycles that have at least one year of service
remaining.
</P>
<P>
At present, China has opened 387 second-hand motor vehicle
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
According to an investigation, about 60 percent of the used
vehicles have been purchased by townships and farmers. The
transactions mainly occur in relatively developed areas and large
cities. 
</P>
