<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Philadelphia Tennis Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 16 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina
Hingis of Switzerland won the 450,000 Advanta Championships
Sunday by defeating fifth-seeded Lindsay Davenport, 7-5, 6-7
(7-9), 7-6 (7-4) in the final at Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
It was the 12th title of the year for Hingis, three of them
coming in Grand Slam events. The 17-year-old Hingis is now 74-4
on the year. It marked the first time in her career that she had
to play four three-set matches in a single tournament.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Davenport, seeded third at the championships,
will move into the No. 2 spot in the world rankings Monday.
</P>
<P>
Davenport was leading 30-0 in the 12th game of the third set
to hold a 6-5 advantage. But Hingis rallied to send the set into
the second straight tiebreak.
</P>
<P>
Hingis is 8-3 on the year in tiebreaks and is 5-3 against
Davenport.
</P>
<P>
Davenport saw her 12-match winning streak come to an end. She
is 59-15 in 1997. Hingis took home 79,000 U.S. dollars for the
victory. 
</P>
